premise_source_doc_sentence: Helen Adams Keller  (  June 27 , 1880 -- June 1 , 1968  )  was an American author , political activist , and lecturer .

Her birthday on June 27 is commemorated as Helen Keller Day in the U.S. state of Pennsylvania and was authorized at the federal level by presidential proclamation by President Jimmy Carter in 1980 , the 100th anniversary of her birth .
A prolific author , Keller was well-traveled and outspoken in her convictions .
A member of the Socialist Party of America and the Industrial Workers of the World , she campaigned for women 's suffrage , labor rights , socialism , antimilitarism , and other similar causes .
